title: Fernhill C1–C4 — Kettle's block and bribe, Tobias's patrol and topics
story: fernhill
description: The guard block (conditional exit on Mrs Kettle's state) lifts on
  the sherry bribe (give-gating, possession-conditioned state change). Tobias
  patrols his route (caught with wait-UNTIL); his topics table answers the
  free-text alias ("the fire"), the entity tier (the boiler, in scope in the
  shed), the red-herring row, and misses fall to his catch-all shrug — never
  appended to a hit. Kettle's second table has NO catch-all: her miss takes
  the stdlib unknown_topic default. The folly door unjams once Tobias is
  shaken.
---

# --- C2: the guard block ---
> north
[OK: contains "Gravel Drive"]

> north
[OK: contains "Fountain Court"]

> north
[OK: contains "Entrance Hall"]

> west
[OK: contains "The study is not for visitors"]
[OK: not contains "leather-topped desk"]

# --- C4 table 2 (Mrs Kettle): entity tier, free-text alias, and the
# no-catch-all miss (stdlib default speaks) ---
> take the grey overcoat
[OK: contains "Taken"]

> ask kettle about the overcoat
[OK: contains "Her walking coat"]

> ask kettle about verity's study
[OK: contains "something that made the evening kinder"]

> ask kettle about the weather
[OK: not contains "knitting"]

# --- C3: the bribe — give the sherry, her state flips, the block lifts ---
> east
[OK: contains "Kitchen"]

> take the sherry bottle
[OK: contains "Taken"]

> west
[OK: contains "Entrance Hall"]

> give the sherry bottle to kettle
[OK: contains "Her ladyship's oloroso"]

> west
[OK: contains "Verity's study"]

> east
[OK: contains "Entrance Hall"]

# --- C1: catch Tobias on his rounds (route: Drive, Court, Shed; wait-turns 5;
# "Tobias arrives." is the patrol announcement) ---
> south
[OK: contains "Fountain Court"]

[DO]
> wait
[OK: contains_any "Time passes" "enters"]
[UNTIL "enters from the"]

# --- C4 table 1 (Tobias): free-text ALIAS hit (the row's primary is
# "the folly") — his answer owns the response; the shrug never appends ---
> ask tobias about the fire
[OK: contains "The door's only warped, not cursed"]
[OK: not contains "spits"]

# Miss → the catch-all shrug (D5's miss path)
> ask tobias about the weather
[OK: contains "spits"]

# Red-herring row: the bank theory dies here
> ask tobias about the bank
[OK: contains "Bank never had it"]

# --- Entity-tier hit: the boiler, asked IN the shed (both in scope) ---
> east
[OK: contains "old coal dust"]

[DO]
> wait
[OK: contains_any "Time passes" "enters"]
[UNTIL "enters from the"]

> ask tobias about the boiler
[OK: contains "Fill her, set the valve, then light"]

# Thaw the way (the A5 condition, live) — full startup order
> turn the stopcock
[OK: contains "water gurgles"]

> push the primer
[OK: contains "thumps home"]

> turn on the boiler
[OK: contains "warmth crawls toward the greenhouse"]

# --- The folly door unjams now that Tobias is shaken ---
> west
[OK: contains "Fountain Court"]

> west
[OK: contains "Glass"]

> north
[OK: contains "Folly Hill"]

> open the folly door
[OK: contains "You open the folly door"]

> north
[OK: contains "Soot still ghosts the walls"]
